FLOW
distance_units   meters
time_units       seconds
calculate_flow   true
permeability_x   8.19e-11   default
permeability_y   8.19e-11   default
pressure         0.00       default

!!!The fixed pressure boundary CANNOT be the zero permeability boundary, or the pressure has no effect
!upper boundary pressure (surface/atmospheric pressure)
pressure         0.0         zone    1-31     32-32    1-1    fix

!no flow lower boundary 
permeability_y   0.00        zone    1-31     0-0    1-1

!no flow left boundary 
permeability_x   0.00        zone    0-0     1-31    1-1

!no flow left boundary 
permeability_x   0.00        zone    32-32     1-31    1-1

!!! You don't need hydrostatic pressure if you are solving for the pressure head (minus the rho*g term)
!lower boundary pressure (hydrostatic pressure at this level)
!!!pressure         30411       zone    1-31     0-0      1-1    fix

!!!  Again, if you have pumping, you don't fix the pressure.  The pressure is determined by the pumping rate.
!injection pressure at the well
!!!pressure         50000       zone    16-16    16-16    1-1    fix

!injection well
!!!  Units of liters/sec
pump  5.0E-4  cementation  16  16  1

!!! There is no point in a fixed pressure if you have zero permeability.  The entire point of a fixed pressure at surface (jy=32)
!!! is to let the water out and to have the pressure dissipate.  Otherwise, you will have a big balloon that bursts.  
!!! You can have any of the sides of the domain open.
!no flow upper boundary (ground level)
!!!permeability_y   0.00        zone    1-31     32-32    1-1
END

